"1186":"1186年","atb 1212":"1212年","1284":"1284年","1150":"1150年","1160":"1160年","Stokenham, Devon, England":"英国戴文斯托肯哈姆","Stokeley, Devon, England":"英国戴文","lifeSummary":"当Sir Robert English于1186年出生在英国戴文斯托肯哈姆时，他的父亲Gilbert De English36岁，母亲Elizabeth Melson27岁。他于1212年之前与Lady Agathe结婚。他们至少是1个女儿的父母。他去世于1212年在他的家乡享年26岁。"},"hr":{"1186–1212":"1186.–1212.","1190–1212":"1190–1212.","1212–1284":"1212.–1284","1150–Male":"1150–preminuo","1160–Female":"1160–preminula","1190":"1190","before 1212":"prije 1212.","1212":"1212.","1186":"1186.","atb 1212":"1212.","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"cs":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Zesnulý","1160–Female":"1160–Zesnulá","1190":"1190","before 1212":"před 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, Anglie","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, Anglie"},"da":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Afdød","1160–Female":"1160–Afdød","1190":"1190","before 1212":"før 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"nl":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Overleden","1160–Female":"1160–Overleden","1190":"1190","before 1212":"vóór 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"en":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Deceased","1160–Female":"1160–Deceased","1190":"1190","before 1212":"before 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"English","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English, Scottish, and Welsh: ethnic name from Middle English <i>English</i>, <i>Inglish</i>, <i>Inglis</i> ‘English’ (Old English <i>Englisc</i>), sometimes alternating with Anglo-Norman French <i>Engleis</i>, <i>Engles</i>, <i>Anglais</i>, <i>Angles</i> (Old French <i>Englois</i>). Compare   Inglis   and   England  . Among the aristocracy and upper gentry it marked out a man of English ancestry from one of Norman or continental origin. In counties bordering England with Scotland and Wales the name distinguished an Englishman from a Scot or a native Welshman on both sides of the border. The name may also have been acquired by English merchants who traded abroad or who lived and worked in a ‘French’ borough in England (one exclusively administered by Normans).","Irish: in Ireland, this name was used to denote an Englishman, often being adopted for Irish <b>Aingléis</b> ‘Englishman’ or through mistranslation for <b>Mac an Ghallóglaigh</b>, see   Gallogly   and   Golightly  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Engles","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Michel, Remi.","English and Scottish: variant of   English   or   Inglis  .","Altered form of German and Dutch   Engels  ."]},{"name":"Inglis","meanings":["Scottish (Lanarkshire and Midlothian): ethnic name from Scots <i>Inglis</i> ‘English(man)’. Compare   English  ."]},{"name":"England","meanings":["English: habitational name from Middle English <i>Engelond</i> ‘England’. It was probably a formal alternative to   English  , which is also well evidenced as a surname in England. These names may have been acquired by English landowners who moved in Norman social circles or who lived in a neighbouring country (Scotland, Wales, or Ireland), or by English merchants who traded abroad.","Norwegian: habitational name from any of various farmsteads so named, from Old Norse <i>eng</i> ‘meadow’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’.","Swedish: ornamental name with the same meaning as 2."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Robert English was born in 1186, in Stokenham, Devon, England, his father, Gilbert De English, was 36 and his mother, Elizabeth Melson, was 27. He married Lady Agathe before 1212. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1212, in his hometown, at the age of 26."},"et":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1160–Female":"1160–Surnud","1190":"1190","before 1212":"enne 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1160–Female":"1160–Kuollut","1190":"1190","before 1212":"ennen vuotta 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1160–Female":"1160–Décédée","1190":"1190","before 1212":"avant 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, Angleterre","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Robert English est né en 1186, à Stokenham, Devon, Angleterre, son père, Gilbert De English, avait 36 ans et sa mère, Elizabeth Melson, avait 27 ans. Il a épousé Lady Agathe avant 1212. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille. Il est décédé en 1212, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 26 ans."},"de":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Verstorben","1160–Female":"1160–Verstorben","1190":"1190","before 1212":"vor 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England","lifeSummary":"Als Sir Robert English 1186 in Stokenham, Devon, England geboren wurde, war sein Vater Gilbert De English 36 und seine Mutter Elizabeth Melson 27. Er hat vor 1212 Lady Agathe geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter. Er starb 1212 im Alter von 26 Jahren in seinem Geburtsort."},"ht":{"1186–1212":"1186–1212","1190–1212":"1190–1212","1212–1284":"1212–1284","1150–Male":"1150–Desede","1160–Female":"1160–Desede","1190":"1190","before 1212":"before 1212","1212":"1212","1186":"1186","atb 1212":"1212","1284":"1284","1150":"1150","1160":"1160","Stokenham, Devon, England":"Stokenham, Devon, England","Stokeley, Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"hu":{"1186–1212":"1186–1